spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:script: Enable('MDIO_PHYID', Eq('GMII_TBI', 'TBI'));\ Tooltip('MDIO_PHYID', 'This parameter is only required when the TBI interface is selected. Valid values are 0 to 31.');\ Tooltip('PACKET_SIZE', 'The Packet Size (PACKET_SIZE) parameter configures the size of the transmit and receive FIFOs used to buffer frame data between the system interface and MAC. PACKET_SIZE parameter drop down list allows to select transmit FIFO size, the receive FIFO is double the size of transmit FIFO. The default of 8Kbytes transmit FIFO can handle the maximum IEEE802.3 Ethernet frames (1522 bytes). Please refer to the handbook for further information.');\ Tooltip('STATS', 'Statistics counters (STATS) function gathers the statistics information on the data transmitted and received. Tick the check box to enable this feature, please refer to the Statistics Counters Registers in Hand Book for further information.');\ Tooltip('SAL', 'Station Address Logic (SAL) function provides the address filtering and multicast or broadcast reception capability. Tick the check box to enable this feature. Please refer to the handbook for further information.');\ Tooltip('WoL', 'Wake On LAN (WOL) Detected function detects the IEEE 802.3 compliant unicast frames with a destination address that matches the station address and packets that use AMD Magic Packet Detection technology. Tick the check box to enable this feature. Please refer to the handbook for further information.');\ Enable('SLIP_ENABLE', And(Eq('FAMILY', 'PolarFire'), Eq('GMII_TBI', 'TBI')));\

spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: Tri-Speed Ethernet MAC core with following features: - Tri-Speed Ethernet MAC Core - 10/100/1000 Mbps Operation - Full-Duplex at 10/100/1000 Mbps - Half-Duplex at 10/100 Mbps - Standard G/MII interface - MDIO interface for PHY register access -Ten-bit interface (TBI) for 1000Base-T or 1000Base-X support - Wake on LAN (WoL) with Magic Packet Detection - Frame Statistics Counters - Destination Address Based Filtering
